Making a journey into the height
The ruins of the fortress Massada form the remains of the secret cache in front of enemies, the Herodes the Large in the year of 25 nth Chr. uplift for his family made.
They are due to a cliff in the mountains in 450 meters height above sea-level.
Only mountain climbers can reach the ruins from own strength.
An air cable railway brings all others to this historical peak.
In the north of the country in 1600 to 2040 meters height is the famous ski field Hermon into which it pulls innumerable tourists in the winter months.
From the foot of the mountain you reach there with a shuttle bus.
The ski runs have an overall length of 45 kilometers.
According to an old legend pagan gods lived supposedly on the mountain top.
