Doing something for the health
The three most important recreation areas of Israel lie near the shores of the Mediterranean Sea, the Red Sea and the Dead Sea.
At each of the three places there are swimming pools, water parks, dolphin arias and oceanariums.
Strange to say swims in the Red sea also in the winter months since the water temperature does not fall to less than 21 °C there and warms up the air to 23 °C.
The Dead Sea is even still more warmly and there baths over the whole year.
After all the way this unusual sea with a situation of 417 meters below sea-level is the most deeply sited sea of the world.
His turquoise blue water has a high salinity and supports even nonswimmers without problems through that on the surface.
The surrounding landscape is indescribably beautiful.
Visitors come here from dermatitis, allergies, asthma, eczemas, arthritis, bronchitis, diabetes and nerves strapazierter for the smoothing, for treatments under application of salt water (natural salt brine) and welfare sludge as well as for the treatment.
Touching the secrets of the antiquity
The old town of Tel Aviv, that is the city of Jaffa, contains these secrets at the Mediterranean Sea coast.
Through this city the famous lake way disappeared which united Egypt, Syria, Anatolia and Mesopotamia with each other.
The city is mentioned in old-Greek and ancient Egyptian legends.
According to traditions Noah just built his ark here, and Perseus saved here the beautiful Andromeda with which it led a long and happy life at this place.
Tourists amble gladly through the narrow lanes which are named after asterisks.
Fortune is supposed to be according to the legend lovely to all who touch the walls in the lane with their asterisk.
In Jaffa you can find newly-married pairs from whole Israel and even other countries at photo appointments.
In Caesarea, the city of king Herodes, you can roam through the roman theater and conquer the fortress of the crusaders.
In the roman time Caesarea was the most important city of Judäas and residence of the roman governors, under that also Pontius Pilatus.
In the carefully restored theater evening concerts and operas are performed nowadays.
